        "jsCode": "// Collapse 118 chunk rows into ONE item containing a list of unique document names.\n// This is critical — without this, the next node (List All Files) would run\n// 118 times (once per chunk row) and produce thousands of duplicate entries.\n\nconst existingNames = $input.all()\n  .map(i => (i.json.DocumentName || '').toLowerCase().trim())\n  .filter(name => name.length > 0);\n\nconst uniqueNames = [...new Set(existingNames)];\n\nconsole.log(`Documents already in knowledge base (${uniqueNames.length}): ${uniqueNames.join(', ')}`);\n\n// Return exactly ONE item — so the next node runs exactly once\nreturn [{ json: { existingDocNames: uniqueNames } }];"
